6 An Act relating to schools; amending 70 O.S. 2021,
Section 5-118, which relates to meetings of district
7 boards of education; allowing a board of education to
submit an affidavit in lieu of meeting minutes in
8 certain circumstances; stating affidavit
requirements; requiring the State Department of
9 Education to accept certain affidavits; clarifying
duty of boards to keep meeting minutes; providing
10 affidavit components; and providing an effective
date.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 5-118, is
15 amended to read as follows:
16 Section 5-118. A. Regular meetings of the board of education
17 of each school district shall be held upon the first Monday of each
18 month, or upon such day as may be fixed by the board. Special
19 meetings may be held from time to time as circumstances may demand.
20 B. All meetings of the boards of education shall be public
21 meetings, and in all such meetings the vote of each member must be
22 publicly cast and recorded. Executive sessions will be permitted
23 only for the purpose of discussing the employment, hiring,
24 appointment, promotion, demotion, disciplining, or resignations of
ENGR. H. B. NO. 1958 Page 1

1 any or all of the employees or volunteers of the school district,
2 and for the purpose of discussing negotiations concerning employees
3 and representatives of employee groups, and for the purpose of
4 hearing evidence and discussing the expulsion or suspension of a
5 student or students only when requested by the student involved or
6 his or her parent, attorney, or legal guardian; provided, however,
7 that any vote or action thereon must be taken in a public meeting
8 with the vote of each member publicly cast and recorded. It is
9 required that the board of education shall provide notice to the
10 student, his or her parent, attorney or legal guardian that said
11 student is entitled to an executive session regarding the discussion
12 of expulsion or suspension of said student.
13 C. Any action taken in violation of the provisions of this act
14 shall be invalid.
15 D. Each member of the board of education of a school district
16 with an average daily attendance exceeding fifteen thousand (15,000)
17 or a school district where boundaries encompass a total population
18 exceeding one hundred thousand (100,000) persons according to the
19 last preceding Federal Decennial Census may be paid from the
20 district's general fund a stipend of Twenty-five Dollars ($25.00)
21 for each regular, special or adjourned meeting of the board of
22 education that he or she attends, but not for more than four
23 meetings in any calendar month.
