1 E. 1. Unless otherwise provided by law, a board of education
2 may submit an Affidavit of Board Action to the State Department of
3 Education in lieu of approved board minutes to provide proof of an
4 action approved or taken at a board meeting. Such affidavit shall
5 be signed and sworn by the applicable personnel as provided in
6 paragraph 2 of this subsection. The State Department of Education
7 shall accept a signed Affidavit of Board Action as certification
8 that the district board has approved or taken a specific action at a
9 board meeting. Nothing in this subsection shall exempt a board of
10 education from keeping minutes of a meeting in accordance with
11 Section 312 of Title 25 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
12 2. The Affidavit of Board Action described in paragraph 1 of
13 this subsection shall include:
14 a. the county or district code,
15 b. the name of the school district,
16 c. the date of the board meeting,
17 d. the agenda item number approved,
18 e. a summary of the action approved,
19 f. an affirming signature representing the district from
20 the district superintendent or the assistant
21 superintendent, and
22 g. an affirming signature representing the district board
23 from the board president or chair, or from a board
24 officer.
